key operational and strategic Army leadership, as well as cutting-edge innovation and emerging technologies to validate seamless, secure, and scalable network

 architecture solutions. The approach emphasizes collaboration with partner stakeholders to ensure access to the latest data and advancements in network integration,
 testing, and validation.

 The program designs and produces focused network architectures with the division as the unit of maneuver while collecting test and user feedback through user
 juries and user evaluations to drive the Army network configuration. Through continuous and iterative acquisition methodologies, TCNE accelerates delivery timelines,
 reduce costs, and creates flexibility for partner network program offices in adapting to evolving mission requirements. Additionally, the strategy prioritizes cybersecurity
 and interoperability to mitigate network threat vulnerabilities to ensure robust and resilient network architectures and increase the lethality and operational needs of
 stakeholders. This comprehensive approach ensures the delivery of high-quality, mission-critical network solutions while driving innovation and efficiency throughout the
 acquisition lifecycle.

 Through support agreements, TCNE leverages Army testing agency services including U.S. Army Test & Evaluation Command (ATEC), and U.S. Army Combat
 Capabilities Development Command (DEVCOM), for verification and validation and lab-based risk reduction of priority system integration and innovation efforts. TCNE
 also procures commercial off the shelf items necessary to test and validate the integration of multiple system and network baselines through various contractual vehicles
 including Common Hardware System 6th Generation (CHS-6), other indefinite delivery/indefinite quantity contracts, and Defense Logistics Agency (DLA).

