FY 2026 Plans:
As the FY 2026 Technology maturation flagship investment, Space Modernization Initiative (SMI) will deliver the final components
needed to meet Missile Warning/Missile Tracking (MW/MT) Enterprise-wide peak production demands for large format, resilient,
high dynamic range Focal Plane Arrays (FPA) and protective filters and coatings for the FPAs. The thrust array will seek to
transition developments for intelligent mission management into MW/MT Epoch 2 in order to merge various stovepipes of satellite
tasking and inject event-based automation to the tasking architecture.

Additionally, technology maturation will continue to propel emerging technologies to include meta optics, edge computing tools,
and neuromorphic imaging in order to meet threats posed by our pacing adversaries in the FY 2030s.
FY 2027 Plans:
Through Technology Maturation, Space Modernization Initiative (SMI) will continue to ensure the final components needed
to meet Missile Warning/Missile Tracking (MW/MT) Enterprise-wide peak production demands for large format, resilient, high
dynamic range infrared Focal Plane Arrays (FPAs) and protective filters and coatings for the FPAs. Advancing the FPA state-of-
the-art is critical for space-based sensing and this thrust directly impacts manufacturability and cost reduction of sensors used
in MW/MT Epochs and Space Development Agency (SDA) Tranches. Effort will involve higher resolution (8K X 8K) sensors for
better tracking capabilities, supply chain resilience and domestic manufacturability, digital in-pixel Read Out Integrated Circuits
(ROICs), and other advancements that provide increased capability and/or lower cost.

The thrust will seek to transition developments into MW/MT Epoch 2 and inform Epoch 3 in order to merge various stovepipes of
satellite tasking and inject event-based automation to the tasking architecture. This thrust will also be used to pursue activities that
investigate the tasking and coordination of sensors across Space Systems Command
(SSC), SDA, and Missile Defense Agency (MDA) assets.

SMI will continue to propel emerging technologies to include more advanced hardened planar array antennas to meet the needs
of Relay Ground Antenna (RGA) and Space-Based Infrared System (SBIRS) Survivable Endurable Evolution (S2E2), meta optics,
edge computing tools, and novel phenomenology sensor development to meet threats posed by our pacing adversaries in FY
2030.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 increased due to realignment of funds from the Demos thrust to the Tech Mat thrust to optimize mission investments.
