Title: Capability Exploitation                                                                                                                    -              -       19.957
Description: Capability Exploitation focuses on fielding, integrating, and operationally employing prototype capabilities derived
from SMI investments to deliver near-term mission value and leave behind residual operational capacity. Unlike demonstrations
that validate technical feasibility, this thrust deliberately designs and executes efforts in operationally relevant environments with
the intent to accelerate learning, inform Concept of Operations (CONOPS), and reduce transition risk to Programs of Record
(PoR).

This thrust adopts a deliberate lean-forward risk posture. Building beyond the Demonstration thrust, activities are structured
to pursue meaningful operational outcomes, even when technical risk remains, with demonstrations intentionally designed to
provide residual mission utility wherever feasible. In this construct, measured risk and iterative learning are acceptable outcomes
if they advance enterprise understanding, inform architecture decisions, and accelerate capability adoption across the Overhead
Persistent Infrared (OPIR) and Resilient Missile Warning Missile Tracking (MW/MT) mission sets. Capability Exploitation is a new
start.

FY 2027 Plans:
Capability Exploitation is a new start. In FY 2027, Capability Exploitation will operationalize the first transition of an Space
Modernization Initiative (SMI)-derived effort into this construct through the ThinKom phased array antenna initiative. Originally
launched to rapidly demonstrate and inform requirements for the Resilient Ground Architecture (RGA), this effort evolved into
a more operationally relevant demonstration with the goal of utility in both Continental United States (CONUS) and Indo-Pacific
Command (INDOPACOM) locations.

Building on this model, the thrust will mature efforts under the emerging program to leverage the growing availability of
commercially hosted platforms, enabling rapid placement of OPIR and MW/MT payloads across diverse space architectures.
Additionally, this effort will identify and pursue opportunities to demonstrate Hypersonic Glide Vehicle (HGV) sensing capabilities
with the intent to both prove feasibility and leave behind operationally relevant sensor contributions wherever possible. These

