A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Project funds will applied to strategically address future force requirements identified in concept documents and organizational structures. PM SMD leverages this
funding to develop and integrate advanced medical solutions that enhance Warfighter survivability and operational effectiveness in support of Capability Program
Executive Ground (Soldier Systems). These efforts ensure the Army remains equipped with cutting-edge medical technologies to meet the demands of modern and
future combat environments. This Program Element represents a vital investment in the Army's medical modernization strategy, enabling the development and fielding of
innovative medical solutions that align with the Army's readiness priorities and sustain the health and effectiveness of the force.

 These funds have transitioned from T2COM (AFC) into ASA(ALT) starting FY26. Requesting project 808 / DoD Drug & Vacc Ad funding to be merged into 836 / Field
 Medical Systems Advanced Development. This will benefit the development, testing, and evaluation of advanced medical technologies and systems that are nearing the
 transition from research and development to operational use. Our primary focus of utilizing this 6.4 funding is on refining prototypes, conducting system integration, and
 ensuring that medical solutions are ready for field deployment for US Army Forces.

