A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This project line is critical to equipping deployable forces with advanced medical systems that improve health outcomes, enhance operational effectiveness, and
sustain Soldier readiness in the most challenging environments. By investing in engineering, manufacturing, and testing, the initiative ensures that lifesaving medical
technologies are field-ready and capable of meeting the demands of modern warfare. Through innovation and collaboration, this effort strengthens the Army's ability to
provide comprehensive medical support, ensuring the well-being and survivability of Soldiers while enhancing the overall effectiveness of battlefield operations. Products
from this project will transition to PE 0604807A (Medical Materiel/Medical Biological Defense Equipment - Eng Dev) /Project 832 (Field Medical Systems Engineering
Development).

 The Blast Overpressure Sensor System (BOSS) project will address tactical integration, product development, data management, medical record integration, operational
 testing and evaluation. The BOSS effort requires more in-depth tactical network integration in order to transfer data from the sensor to the data repository and eventually
 to the medical record.

