FY 2027 Plans:
Continue to provide development support and conduct in-depth analysis of medical device component integration into mobile
platforms and shelters. This effort focuses on enhancing the operational capabilities of deployable medical systems, ensuring they
are equipped to deliver advanced care in austere and dynamic environments. By integrating cutting-edge medical technologies
into mobile platforms, we aim to improve the efficiency, reliability, and adaptability of medical shelters, enabling them to better
support the health and readiness of military personnel during mission. The development and integration of medical devices into
mobile platforms, combined with the advancement of the BOSS system, will significantly enhance the Army's ability to monitor,
understand, and address the health impacts of operational hazards. These efforts not only improve immediate care capabilities
but also contribute to the long-term health and readiness of military personnel.
