FY 2026 Plans:
FY 2026 STE-SW (TSS/TMT and NGC) funding will focus on the U.S. Army's priorities for acceleration of NGC Corps capability
to include continuous improvements and development of initial constructive capability in FY26. NGC develops constructive
capabilities to train against a hybrid threat contesting joint force in all five domains of space, cyber, land, air, and maritime.
Initiates Combined Arms Movement and Maneuver exercises for leaders, staffs, and units to integrate the employment of
combined arms capabilities from across the Warfighting Functions (WfFs) against hybrid threat contesting US dominance in all
domains. Additionally, TSS/TMT continues concurrency with Reconfigurable Virtual Collective Trainer (RVCT) platforms and
integration of Avionics Software Emulation (AvSE). Funding supports STE-SW development of iterative incremental capability,
testing and capability releases to accelerate NGC Corps capabilities in the following areas:

-- NGC Sustainment Modeling and Simulation: Model the Sustainment Warfighter Function (WfF) with sufficient detail to drive staff
sustainment planning processes.
-- NGC Intelligence and Electronic Warfare: model jamming attacks on Radars, Precision Munitions, Unmanned Systems, and
IEDs. The intelligence model generate intelligence reports from sensors attached to designated platforms in the simulation.

