A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This Program Element (PE) implements Executive Order (EO) 14299 - Deploying Advanced Nuclear Reactor Technologies for National Security - The United States
faces a critical national security imperative to ensure a resilient, secure, and reliable energy supply for critical defense facilities designated under section 824o-1(c)
of title 16, United States Code, and other mission capability resources. It is the policy of the United States to ensure the rapid development, deployment, and use of
advanced nuclear technologies to support national security objectives, such as the protection and operation of critical infrastructure, critical defense facilities, and other
mission capability resources. The Secretary of the Army serves as the Department of War (DoW) Executive Agent (EA) for both installation and operational nuclear
energy, will lead and begin planning for deployment of Microreactor Power Plants (MPPs). With this funding, the United States will for the first time deploy MPPs at
scale, turning the nation into the global leader in installation and operational nuclear energy.

