D. Acquisition Strategy
Costs related to this MPP program proposal are estimated based on responsibilities for running a program management office for multiple power production plants that
will provide reliable power and key mission energy security on U.S. military installations, reducing financial risks to selective manufacturers. MPPs costs are estimates
for milestone payment for design maturity, licensing and regulatory processes, investment towards key long lead components, and heavy manufacturing capabilities.
This lowers the cost of capital, leading to more affordable electricity and enhances our energy security by providing additional baseload power generation in partnership
with our serving utility providers, improving system reliability for all customers in a given utility service territory, which aligns with 10 USC 2920, Energy Resilience and
Energy Security Measures on Military Installations. This will be coordinated with all the Services to ensure that these reactors go to Army, Air Force, and Navy locations,
on a minimum of 5 different locations. Army will lead program management and the acquisition/oversight process in coordination with ARRO to license the reactors.




