D. Acquisition Strategy
The Common Tactical Truck (CTT) Family of Vehicles (FoVs) is a modernization effort to replace the Line Haul, HEMTT, and PLS vehicles. The CTT began with an
approved Abbreviated Capability Development Document (A-CDD) and was approved to pursue the Middle-Tier of Acquisition (MTA) Rapid Prototyping (RP) pathway
with an anticipated transition to a new Major Capability Acquisition program for Low-Rate Initial Production. The rapid prototyping effort was executed as a competitive
OTA, awarded to four offerors to deliver three prototypes and three digital designs/studies. The Operational Demonstration and prototype assessments informed the
Capability Development Document (CDD).




