Title: MEMSS Prototyping                                                                                                                       -        1.453          0.219
Description: The MEMSS hardware effort will secure Commercial-Off-The-Shelf (COTS) and Government-Off-The-Shelf (GOTS)
components to rapidly explore and refine the technical feasibility of a Radio Frequency (RF) Technical Effects capability. This
effort will focus on integrating and evaluating key technologies to inform the integration of minimum viable products. This will allow
the program to explore the hardware trade-space decisions required to meet operational relevance within affordability targets.

FY 2026 Plans:
FY 2026 funding will support the acquisition and integration of specific COTS components, including Software Defined Radios,
RF amplifiers, and antennas used to broadcast the effect generated by the software effort. Efforts will be conducted in iterative
feedback improvement cycles, focusing on demonstrating key RF Technical Effects capabilities through laboratory testing and
limited field evaluations.
FY 2027 Plans:
FY2027 funding will support the acquisition and integration of COTS Software Defined Radios, RF amplifiers, and antennas
used to broadcast the effect generated by the software effort. Efforts will be conducted in iterative feedback improvement cycles,
focusing on demonstrating key RF Technical Effects capabilities through laboratory testing and limited field evaluations.
